Class FSBlobStore

All Implemented Interfaces:
BlobStore
public class FSBlobStore
extends AbstractBlobStore

Filesystem-backed BlobStore implementation.

This is a non-transactional store that provides read/write access to blobs in a given base directory on the local filesystem.

Blob Ids

Blob ids are file: URIs that specify a file path relative to the store's base directory. Paths may include ".." segments, but cannot specify files outside the store's base directory. For example:
  • Good: file:path/to/file.txt
  • Good: file:path/../file.txt
  • Bad: file:///absolute/path/to/file.txt
  • Bad: file:path/../../file-outside-base.txt
  • Bad: file:path/to/dir/

Id Generation

This store does not support id generation.

Canonical Ids

All Blobs provided by this store will return a non-null value from Blob.getCanonicalId(). The canonical id is the normalized form of the original id, according to the following rules:
  • ".." segments are resolved.
  • "." segments are removed.
  • adjacent "/" characters replaced with a single "/".
  • scheme normalized to lowercase

Author:
Chris Wilper

Method Detail

openConnection

public BlobStoreConnection openConnection(Transaction tx,
                                          Map<String,String> hints)
Description copied from interface: BlobStore
Opens a connection to the blob store.

If the blob store is transactional, the caller must provide a Transaction. Once provided, the connection will be valid for the life of the transaction, at the end of which it will be automatically close()'d.

If the blob store is not transactional, the caller must provide null. Once provided, the connection will be valid until explicitly closed.

Implementations are expected to do any desired pooling of underlying connections themselves.

Parameters:
tx - the transaction associated with this connection, or null if the blob store is not transactional
hints - A set of hints to allow the implementation to optimize the operation (can be null)
Returns:
the connection to the blob store
